The taxi they were travelling in crashed into another vehicle in Durban west. JOHANNESBURG - More than 20 children have been injured in a taxi collision in KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. The taxi they were travelling in crashed into another vehicle in Durban west. One adult and 23 pupils sustained minor injuries. Netcare 911's Shawn Herbst said: “Once treated, all the patients were transported to the hospital for further assessment.”